1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
In this lesson, we will talk about permalinks and also explore permalinks settings.

2
00:00:05,800 --> 00:00:08,800
Here are the learning outcomes.

3
00:00:07,400 --> 00:00:10,400
Number one, defining permalinks and slugs.

4
00:00:10,160 --> 00:00:13,160
Number two, changing permalinks using the built-in WordPress settings.

5
00:00:14,040 --> 00:00:17,040
Number three, modifying category and tag links and lastly, redirecting links using a plugin.

6
00:00:20,280 --> 00:00:23,280
So let's get started.

7
00:00:22,040 --> 00:00:25,040
What are permalinks?

8
00:00:23,720 --> 00:00:26,720
Permalinks stand for permanent links.

9
00:00:26,760 --> 00:00:29,760
They are the permanent URLs that point to a specific page or post.

10
00:00:32,020 --> 00:00:35,020
And the latter part of your URL that comes after the domain name is called the slug.

11
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:40,000
They are user-friendly names to help search engines and users to understand the content

12
00:00:41,600 --> 00:00:44,600
of the page.

13
00:00:43,400 --> 00:00:46,400
Slugs tend to be very similar to their original title of the post or page, or exactly the

14
00:00:47,600 --> 00:00:50,600
same.

15
00:00:48,600 --> 00:00:51,600
And take note, if a title is more than one word, spaces are replaced by a hyphen, as

16
00:00:53,640 --> 00:00:56,640
the example here.

17
00:00:55,040 --> 00:00:58,040
Let's see this in action and open one of the pages on the front end of my website.

18
00:01:01,800 --> 00:01:04,800
When we take a closer look at the permalink, we will see the permalink ends with the name

19
00:01:06,120 --> 00:01:09,120
of the page, namely the slug.

20
00:01:09,640 --> 00:01:12,640
Now we are going to focus our attention on posts.

21
00:01:12,280 --> 00:01:15,280
So let's open up our first post, The World is your Oyster, and as you will see, the

22
00:01:19,680 --> 00:01:22,680
permalink has a date as well as the name of the post.

23
00:01:24,880 --> 00:01:27,880
Let's take a closer look at the permalink settings for our site.

24
00:01:30,120 --> 00:01:33,120
When we are in our dashboard, we will make our way to settings and then click on Permalinks.

25
00:01:38,240 --> 00:01:41,240
Below Common Settings, we will see that the default settings for WordPress is "Day and

26
00:01:42,040 --> 00:01:45,040
Name".

27
00:01:43,040 --> 00:01:46,040
But what does that mean?

28
00:01:44,920 --> 00:01:47,920
It means that the slug of a page will include the name of the page, but the slug of a blog

29
00:01:50,720 --> 00:01:53,720
post will include the date as well as the name of the post.

30
00:01:55,040 --> 00:01:58,040
Let's change the setting to "Only Display the Post Name".

31
00:01:59,160 --> 00:02:02,160
You can also select one of the other options available or create your own custom structure

32
00:02:03,240 --> 00:02:06,240
using their available tags.

33
00:02:05,880 --> 00:02:08,880
Once you have saved your changes, let's go back to our website to see how the permalink

34
00:02:09,720 --> 00:02:12,720
structure for a blog post has changed.

35
00:02:15,600 --> 00:02:18,600
When we take a closer look at the permalink we will see that the date is no longer there.

36
00:02:20,480 --> 00:02:23,480
Next, you also have the option to change the permalink of an individual post or page.

37
00:02:27,280 --> 00:02:30,280
I've created a new blog post and called it "Be on guard and vigilant as there are

38
00:02:31,880 --> 00:02:34,880
pickpockets anywhere and everywhere."

39
00:02:35,880 --> 00:02:38,880
And once we open our blog post, we have quite a long permalink.

40
00:02:40,840 --> 00:02:43,840
Let's modify that to make it more user friendly.

41
00:02:44,560 --> 00:02:47,560
Let's return to our dashboard, open the post and in the sidebar settings click on the URL.

42
00:02:55,080 --> 00:02:58,080
The URL slug is the entire name of the post.

43
00:02:58,840 --> 00:03:01,840
So let's replace that by typing in Pickpockets only.

44
00:03:03,080 --> 00:03:06,080
And once we click on Update, we can view the post on the front end and now the slug only

45
00:03:09,360 --> 00:03:12,360
displays 'pickpockets.'

46
00:03:11,880 --> 00:03:14,880
Lastly, let's discuss permalinks for categories and tags.

47
00:03:18,480 --> 00:03:21,480
Let's open the World is your Oyster post.

48
00:03:21,280 --> 00:03:24,280
Scroll down and here you will see a category called Travel and a tag called Adventure.

49
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:31,000
Let's click on Travel.

50
00:03:30,040 --> 00:03:33,040
This page will of course display all posts that have been assigned to the travel category.

51
00:03:35,640 --> 00:03:38,640
And the permalink will include the word 'category' and then the name of the category in this

52
00:03:40,440 --> 00:03:43,440
case 'travel.'

53
00:03:42,960 --> 00:03:45,960
But if we go to permalink settings, we can actually change the word 'category' or 'tag.'

54
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:52,520
At the bottom below optional, it says if you like, you may enter custom structures for

55
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:57,960
your category and tag URLs here.

56
00:03:57,280 --> 00:04:00,280
So instead of saying 'categories', we can change it to something like 'topics.'

57
00:04:03,080 --> 00:04:06,080
And instead of your tag permalink saying 'tags', it can say 'key words' for example.

58
00:04:08,200 --> 00:04:11,200
To see this applied on the front end, let's open up the World is your Oyster post.

59
00:04:12,760 --> 00:04:15,760
Scroll down and then click on the travel category.

60
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:21,800
The permalink now says 'topics' and 'travel' and not 'categories' and 'travel' anymore.

61
00:04:24,240 --> 00:04:27,240
Finally, we have to talk about redirecting permalinks.

62
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:32,000
Make sure you only change link structures when a blog post or page is new.

63
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:37,480
If you change an old permalink on an established website, visitors will not automatically be

64
00:04:39,240 --> 00:04:42,240
redirected to the new link.

65
00:04:42,520 --> 00:04:45,520
So if you don't want to affect your search engine ranking or traffic to your established

66
00:04:47,360 --> 00:04:50,360
site, you need to make sure you install a plugin to redirect your old URLs.

67
00:04:53,240 --> 00:04:56,240
Let's make our way to plugins, add new and in the search box, type in 'Redirect links.'

68
00:05:04,440 --> 00:05:07,440
There are different options to choose from, but I'm going to install an open source plugin

69
00:05:11,240 --> 00:05:14,240
called Redirection.

70
00:05:13,680 --> 00:05:16,680
When you are ready, click on Install and then activate the plugin.

71
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:21,800
Once the plugin is installed, click on Settings.

72
00:05:24,080 --> 00:05:27,080
Then go ahead and click on Start Setup.

73
00:05:28,080 --> 00:05:31,080
And once you have gone through all the steps, you can click on Ready to Begin.

74
00:05:34,080 --> 00:05:37,080
When you are on the options page, click on Redirects top left.

75
00:05:38,720 --> 00:05:41,720
And here you can redirect old URLs.

76
00:05:42,200 --> 00:05:45,200
The source URL refers to your old permalink or URL.

77
00:05:47,080 --> 00:05:50,080
And the target URL is your new URL that you will be using.

78
00:05:50,920 --> 00:05:53,920
Let's use our pickpocket post as an example.

79
00:05:54,280 --> 00:05:57,280
So next to source URL, enter the old permalink.

80
00:06:01,240 --> 00:06:04,240
And next to target URL, let's paste our new permalink.

81
00:06:05,600 --> 00:06:08,600
And when you are ready, add redirect.

82
00:06:10,200 --> 00:06:13,200
So now when somebody clicks on your old link on an established site, they will be redirected

83
00:06:15,120 --> 00:06:18,120
to the new URL.

84
00:06:17,960 --> 00:06:20,960
I trust you now have a better grasp on managing your Permalinks.

